<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Forty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Forty,</orth> four times ten: <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.159" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 4</bibl>. Used for an indefinite number, where no exact reckoning was needed: <cit><quote>when f. winters shall besiege thy brow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 2, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I had rather than f. shillings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 205</bibl></cit>; <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 20</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. tn 5.180.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 180</bibl>. <cit><quote>f. more,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>worth f. ducats,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 84</bibl></cit>. 97; cf. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.95" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 95</bibl>. 117 and <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 4, 14</bibl>. <cit><quote>in f. minutes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 176</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. fancies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I myself fight not once in f. year,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. pence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 89</bibl></cit> (proverbial expression of a small wager). <cit><quote>within these f. hours,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.253" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 253</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. truncheoners,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I could beat f. of them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.243" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 243</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hop f. paces,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 234</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. days longer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>is not the king's name f. thousand names?</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 85</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>twenty</emph>). <cit><quote>f. thousand fathom above water,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.281" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 281</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. thousand brothers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.292" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 292</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. thousand lives,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.442" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 442</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>